(8353, 414, '_google_reviews_4_caption', 'field_63ae92b97ece8'),
(8354, 414, 'google_reviews_4_description', 'Dear Sir, I am very thankful and glad that I made a firm decision to join Uptas. Without your guidance, I would probably still be feeling very demoralised about my chemistry grade and continue getting F9 in school. Before tuition, I was told by everyone that Chemistry was all about memorising and it is a difficult subject that I will never do well or even understand. But you made me fall in love with Chemistry and realised it is a interesting subject that required little memorising. From my most lousy subject, it became one of my favourite subjects!\r\n\r\nYou have definitely made me more confident in tackling chemistry questions and the skills picked up picked up during lessons are indeed very valuable to me. This is quite extreme but honestly,  I think that I can just forgo school lessons and just attend Uptas lessons. I look forward to every lesson not only because they were interesting, but because it was useful. I really like the real life examples you shared during lessons. The improvement from F9 to A2 at O levels, within a short span of time would not be possible without your help. I really loved the way you teach, admire your burning passion for Chemistry and you are really funny. Thanks for connecting my dots in Chemistry!'),
