(9474, 514, 'google_reviews_1_name', 'Isabel Joy Kua (TKGS, VJC)'),
(9475, 514, '_google_reviews_1_name', 'field_63ae92a67ece7'),
(9476, 514, 'google_reviews_1_caption', 'My chemistry grades improved to an A1 in O level'),
(9477, 514, '_google_reviews_1_caption', 'field_63ae92b97ece8'),
(9478, 514, 'google_reviews_1_description', 'Since Secondary Three my Chemistry was never too good. I failed Chemistry twice in Sec Three(2015) and got C5 for the other two exams. I decided to join two of my other friends for Uptas Chemistry tuition after getting a C5 for my CA1. Joining this tuition was a wonderful decision as classes with the tutors in Uptas was always extremely fun and enjoyable as well as extremely enriching.\r\n\r\nI always left class with more understanding of the Chemistry concepts and answers to my questions. Soon enough, my chemistry grades improved to a B4 for Mid Years, a B3 for Prelims and then an A1 for O Levels. Tutors in Uptas are a very patient tutor, never failing to answer our countless questions as well as encourage us when we didn’t do well for tests. His positive spirit motivates us to pick ourselves up after each failure and to go forward toward success. I would definitely recommend Uptas for those who needs chemistry tuition!'),
(9479, 514, '_google_reviews_1_description', 'field_63ae92c97ece9'),
(9480, 514, 'google_reviews_2_image', '469'),
(9481, 514, '_google_reviews_2_image', 'field_63ae926d7ece6'),
(9482, 514, 'google_reviews_2_name', 'Sally (TKGS, VJC)'),
(9483, 514, '_google_reviews_2_name', 'field_63ae92a67ece7'),
(9484, 514, 'google_reviews_2_caption', 'Lessons in Uptas are interesting and engaging as the tutors tries his best to simplify chemistry concepts'),
(9485, 514, '_google_reviews_2_caption', 'field_63ae92b97ece8'),
(9486, 514, 'google_reviews_2_description', 'The tutors in Uptas are very dedicated teacher who is concerned about his students’ progress and adopts an effective learning system during his lessons. This includes being technologically savvy, using a projector instead of traditional white board which facilitates our learning as we students are able to see the content on the screen easily as opposed to using a whiteboard, which may be time consuming. Lessons in Uptas are interesting and engaging as the tutors tries his best to simplify chemistry concepts that are difficult to understand for better understanding and show us videos helpful to our learning when necessary such as videos on crystallization so as to let us visualize and understand the process and steps to take instead of just blindly memorizing from textbooks, where the content takes a longer time to sink into our heads. The tutors in Uptas also provides us with useful resources such as concise notes and a laminated periodic table with equations and other content compiled on a single page which allows us to refer to them and study more efficiently especially when exams are near.\r\n\r\nApart from adopting a positive attitude and encouraging us to never give up, the regular practices of worksheets and the provision of challenging questions from other school’s papers also enabled me to maintain a consistent grade of A1 throughout my secondary 4 years. He is also one of the most patient teachers I’ve ever had and encourages us to ask questions whenever in doubt even through platforms such as Whatsapp, and strives to reply to us as quickly as possible with detailed explanations. I definitely owe my great improvement in Chemistry to Dr. Aw as he was the teacher who spurred my interest in Chemistry and made me enjoy learning the subject.'),
(9487, 514, '_google_reviews_2_description', 'field_63ae92c97ece9'),
(9488, 514, 'google_reviews_3_image', '471'),
(9489, 514, '_google_reviews_3_image', 'field_63ae926d7ece6'),
(9490, 514, 'google_reviews_3_name', 'TAN RONG HUI, TMJC'),
(9491, 514, '_google_reviews_3_name', 'field_63ae92a67ece7'),
(9492, 514, 'google_reviews_3_caption', 'Thank you for helping me get an A for chemistry which is nothing short of a miracle!'),
(9493, 514, '_google_reviews_3_caption', 'field_63ae92b97ece8'),
(9494, 514, 'google_reviews_3_description', 'Before entering JC, I was warned by many that A level Chemistry was going to be tough. That was when my sister recommended me to you. I’m a very logical person, things has to clear to me like, How can this tuition help me achieve my A in Chemistry? What resources can the teachers provided, which are superior to those given in school? You made me realise that chemistry was not as challenging and inaccessible as I initially thought to be. You were patient and knowledgeable, able to give precise explanation any clarity any doubts. Your notes and teachings were really easy to understand and learn.\r\n\r\nThank you for building the perfect foundation for my Chemistry. Thank you for helping me get an A for chemistry which is nothing short of a miracle! All I needed is a little effort on my part and the A was mine. I will want you as your Chemistry tutor, because really, you are really an awesome teacher. Not only because of how capable you are, but because you truly have a heart for your students. I wouldn’t have conquered survived Chemistry without your help. Joining Uptas became easily one of the best decisions I have ever made in my life. In just one lesson, I could understand the concepts, link topics together and remember things. Chemistry was made more interesting with the detailed explanations!'),
(9495, 514, '_google_reviews_3_description', 'field_63ae92c97ece9'),
(9496, 514, 'google_reviews_4_image', '472'),
(9497, 514, '_google_reviews_4_image', 'field_63ae926d7ece6'),
(9498, 514, 'google_reviews_4_name', 'SEAN CHAI, Victoria School'),
(9499, 514, '_google_reviews_4_name', 'field_63ae92a67ece7'),
(9500, 514, 'google_reviews_4_caption', 'You made me fall in love with Chemistry and realised it is a interesting subject that required little memorising'),
(9501, 514, '_google_reviews_4_caption', 'field_63ae92b97ece8'),
(9502, 514, 'google_reviews_4_description', 'Dear Sir, I am very thankful and glad that I made a firm decision to join Uptas. Without your guidance, I would probably still be feeling very demoralised about my chemistry grade and continue getting F9 in school. Before tuition, I was told by everyone that Chemistry was all about memorising and it is a difficult subject that I will never do well or even understand. But you made me fall in love with Chemistry and realised it is a interesting subject that required little memorising. From my most lousy subject, it became one of my favourite subjects!\r\n\r\nYou have definitely made me more confident in tackling chemistry questions and the skills picked up picked up during lessons are indeed very valuable to me. This is quite extreme but honestly,  I think that I can just forgo school lessons and just attend Uptas lessons. I look forward to every lesson not only because they were interesting, but because it was useful. I really like the real life examples you shared during lessons. The improvement from F9 to A2 at O levels, within a short span of time would not be possible without your help. I really loved the way you teach, admire your burning passion for Chemistry and you are really funny. Thanks for connecting my dots in Chemistry!'),
